This paper is primarily focused on the design and analysis of an autoscaling algorithm for 5G mobile networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the budget-performance tradeoff, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) or systems and control (cs.SY). The analytical model developed in the paper could be considered as a form of data analysis and statistics (cs.DS), and the simulations conducted to validate the model could be categorized under performance (cs.PF).
